Trade Adjustment Assistance (TAA) is available to workers who lost their jobs as a result of increased imports or a shift of production to other countries. A petition must be certified by the U.S. Department of Labor for individuals to be eligible for services and benefits.
A petition may be filed by:
• a group of three or more workers;
• an official of a certified/recognized union or other representative;
• an official of the employer/firm;
• a Workforce Innovation and Opportunity Act (WIOA) officer;
• GDOL career center staff; or
• Trade Adjustment Unit
Instructions for filing a petition can be found online at etareports.doleta.gov/petition. The petition may be filed online or by using the Petition for Trade Assistance form (ETA-9042). The petition must be filed no later than one year after your job separation date.
